headline: Why Trimble (TRMB) Is Up 6.6% After 2025 Results, 2026 Outlook And Capital Plans
summary: In early February 2026, Trimble Inc. reported full-year 2025 results with revenue of US$3,587.3 million and net income of US$424.0 million, issued 2026 guidance calling for US$3,810.0–US$3,910.0 million in revenue and GAAP EPS of US$2.04–US$2.23, and outlined capital allocation plans emphasizing share repurchases and M&A. Management underscored a focus on tuck-in acquisitions in construction software, rising recurring revenue from its Connect & Scale approach, and AI-enabled productivity...
